cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.SI

This paper presents a deep learning approach for monitoring heart conditions from ECG signals, which involves the detection and classification of abnormal heartbeats. The use of topological data analysis as the basis of the multichannel architecture is a novel aspect of the approach. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves image processing techniques, which could place it in the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. Finally, the use of a modular neural network could also place it in the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
